HEADWORD: Mudhole
<hw>Mud"hole`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A hole,
or hollow place, containing mud, as in a road.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Steam Boilers)</fld> <def>A hole near the bottom,
through which the sediment is withdrawn.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mudir</ent>⟦br⟧
